race.comment: PLEASING SMILE (10) is knocking on the door with consecutive runner-up finishes, missing by a nose at Wodonga two back and hitting the line strongly to get within a head at Tatura last time. Back in trip again here is interesting but he'll be very hard to hold out. SETHEUS (3) is another close to breaking through, no match for A Diva last start at Sale but that form has held up well with the winner winning easily again since. Off a let up for this here but should take beating. LORD CODA (9) is going well, perhaps unsuited coming back in trip at Tatura last time, but still working home well. Drawn to effect here and is in the mix. ZWASP (4) was awful last time at Cranbourne but had been good prior at Sale and could bounce back. CALYPSO KING (1) was okay fresh and can improve.
